<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#fff5ba" WIDTH="150"><B>Procedural History</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">Jack D. Ringwalt and other taxpayers[1]<BR ALIGN='left'/>appeal from the district court&#x27;s[2]<BR ALIGN='left'/>judgment disallowing their claims for<BR ALIGN='left'/>income tax refunds for the year 1967. In<BR ALIGN='left'/>this appeal appellants contend the<BR ALIGN='left'/>district court erred in concluding that<BR ALIGN='left'/>certain corporate transactions<BR ALIGN='left'/>constituted a corporate reorganization<BR ALIGN='left'/>rather than a liquidation producing more<BR ALIGN='left'/>favorable tax treatment.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
>]
